Job Description:
We are currently looking for highly skilled and motivated senior Vietnamese lawyers with the following key skills and responsibilities:

Key professional skills:
The successful candidate will have a proven track record of advising clients on complex foreign investment matters in Vietnam, specifically in the areas of:
 Corporate Law (Vietnamese Enterprise & Investment Regulations);
 Regulatory & Compliance

Responsibilities:
- Provide legal advisory services to the firm’s international clients at the highest level of quality and effectiveness.
- Advise clients on all fields of law that are relevant to foreign invested entities and their op-erations in Vietnam.
- Liaise with relevant authorities for licensing and trouble-shooting purposes, communicate with clients, suppliers, etc. when necessary and as mandated by clients;
- Manage legal (and tax) projects for Luther’s clients independently;
- Lead varying teams of junior to mid-level lawyers (and tax advisors) to professional excel-lence;
- Supervise other team members during the implementation of advisory/project work;
- Perform other legal and management tasks as assigned by the Vietnam office Country Head.
- Train junior lawyers in practical and theoretical aspects of transactional and advisory work;
- Control the output quality of legal advice and other work products of the firm;
- Develop the firm’s business and professional practice by representing Luther Vietnam as a senior legal professional in the market (Business Development & Acquisition).

Job Requirements:
We are looking for a Vietnamese-qualified senior lawyer with a minimum of 12-15 years of post-qualification work experience (PQE) preferably gained in an international work environment (in-ternational law firm experience is preferred).

The following requirements are mandatory:
- Certified graduate from a renowned Vietnamese university working for a private law practice in Vietnam;
- Vietnam-qualified lawyer certificate/bar admission (additional offshore bar admission in a foreign jurisdiction would be an asset).
- Proven knowledge and experience working on complex legal cross-border matters.
- Exceptional skills (oral and written) in English and Vietnamese (additional language proficiency in other foreign languages will be considered an asset).
- Unwavering team spirit, providing strong guidance to colleagues in all advice to clients;
- Professionalism, confidence, dedication, integrity and trustworthiness;
- Ability to manage and lead other team members/junior lawyers in assigned projects;
- Ability to work in an international and multi-cultural team that expands across various jurisdictions;
- Self-starter attitude, high sense of responsibility and ownership in all (internal and external) matters;
- Ability to multitask under high pressure, to complete assignments within time con-straints and deadlines;
- Long-term commitment to the firm and its clients.

The ideal candidate will have a proven track record of in-depth experience in the following fields of business law:

o Foreign investment law/enterprise law (focus on Vietnam FDI),
o Mergers & Acquisitions;
o Enterprise and commercial law,
o Labor law,
o Real estate, construction, and land rights,
o Licensing procedures for enterprise establishment in Vietnam,
o International arbitration and litigation,
o Intellectual property rights and trademark law,
o Tax and customs regulations,
o Import/export procedures,
o Competition and anti-trust law,
o PPP law,
o Environmental law,
o etc.

*Benefits
- Competitive salary (based on relevant work experience and professional qualifica-tions);
- Comprehensive private health insurance;
- 13th monthly salary and annual performance-based bonuses;
- Annual salary reviews/raises based on professional performance and individual success;
- Fast professional development and career progression/promotion;
- Prime office location in the heart of Ho Chi Minh City;
- Above-average annual leave allowance;
- Opportunity to work in an international law firm with well-known and prestigious international clients;
- Gain experience across various legal practice areas under supervision of interna-tional legal experts;
- High level of responsibility and independence in handling client matters.

