• Chịu trách nhiệm trước Ban lãnh đạo THACO AGRI về các mục tiêu chất lượng, hiệu quả sản xuất và an toàn lao động.

Job Requirements:
1. Trình độ chuyên môn: Tốt nghiệp Đại học trở lên các chuyên ngành: Dược học, Hóa học, Công nghệ sinh học,…
2. Kinh nghiệm: Tối thiểu từ 08 năm kinh nghiệm làm việc ở vị trí tương đương tại các Công ty, Tập đoàn có quy mô lớn.
3. Thái độ làm việc: Tích cực, trách nhiệm, tôn trọng và tuân thủ hệ thống quản trị của THACO và THACO AGRI; Ý thức thay đổi và quản trị sự thay đổi.
4. Năng lực:
• Có tư duy quản trị hệ thống tổ chức;
• Có năng lực quản lý và phát triển đội nhóm.
• Có kiến thức và am hiểu sâu về quy trình chế biến dược liệu theo tiêu chuẩn GMP, GACP;
• Có khả năng vận hành, cải tiến dây chuyền chế biến và hệ thống kiểm soát chất lượng;
• Kỹ năng soạn thảo quy trình, trình bày, thuyết trình;
• Kỹ năng Ứng dụng Công nghệ thông tin, Chuyển đổi số và Tiếng Anh vào công việc.
5. Yêu cầu công tác: Ưu tiên ứng viên có khả năng công tác dài ngày tại Campuchia/Lào.

Job Description:
Duty Station: Hanoi, Viet Nam
Contract duration: ASAP until 31 March 2028

Main tasks and responsibilities:
• Support the project team to prepare and implement project activities in the areas of climate change adapatation and mitigation and biodiversity conservation;
• Contribute to the IKI Interface function of the project by preparing articles for the IKI newsletter and events for IKI community in Viet Nam;
• Conduct data collection and analyses in support of development concept notes for activities and events;
• Support the preparation and implementation of the project’s activities in the area of climate policy, NDC and MRV;
• Contribute to the development of an e-learning course to operate the adaptation M&E system for the agriculture sector;
• Overall support for consultant contracting and management, trainings, workshops, partner meetings and other events;
• Undertake additional tasks assigned by the project manager to support the successful implementation of the VN – SIPA II project in the area of national climate policy.

Job Requirements:
Minimum requirements:
• Master degree in environment, climate, agriculture, international relations or other related academic subject;
• Minimum 1 years’ professional experience;
• Initial expertise and interest in the project’s topics, especially related to climate change adaptation and mitigation/climate policy;
• Working experience in development cooperation and/ or in the Vietnamese public sector would be an advantage;
• Knowledge of the international climate negotiations and debate would be an advantage;
• Teamwork ability, dynamic, self-motivated character and interest in development work;
• Excellent written and oral communication skills in English and Vietnamese, with analytical capacities and ability to synthesise relevant findings;
• Excellent command of MS Office and good working knowledge of modern IT applications;
• Excellent self-management and coordination skills, interest in development work;
• Creativity, proactivity and proper initiative towards the results of the project;
• Excellent ability to share knowledge and experience, a good team player;
• Demonstrated ability to work and produce - sometimes under high pressure - high quality outputs.

GIZ is committed to create an appreciative work environment, irrespective of age, ethnic background and nationality, gender and gender identity, physical and mental abilities, religion and worldview, sexual orientation and social background. We ensure human resource processes live up to the diverse competencies and talents of all employees, as well as satisfy our performance expectations.

What we can offer to the successful candidates:
• Good working environment;
• Competitive compensation and benefit packages such as contribution of all compulsory insurances, providing with the additional health care, the annual health check-up and the 24-hours accident insurance;
• Covering all travel expenses with travel allowances when traveling on business;
• And good policy on training and development;
• And policy on flexible working time.

Interested qualified candidates are invited to send the GIZ Application Form in English, copies of relevant certificates and references, either by email or by post (to GIZ Office Hanoi, 6th Floor Hanoi Towers, 49 Hai Ba Trung Street, Hanoi, Vietnam) before 9th November 2025.

Note: Please state “Application for the Junior Project Officer in Climate Change_VN SIPA II” in the subject line or on the envelope. The short-listed candidates will be contacted within 4 weeks after the deadline. Telephone contact is not encouraged.

